{
  "game:characterclass-fighter-knight": "Fighter: Knight",
  "game:characterdesc-fighter-knight": "A bulwark between the people and the dangers of the land. Knights stand steadfast and serve as the core of the fighting force with organization and honor.",

  "game:characterclass-fighter-berserker": "Fighter: Berserker",
  "game:characterdesc-fighter-berserker": "A single-minded fighter interested only in striking down their opponents. Berserkers often eschew armor as it only slows them down and delays their bloodshed.",

  "game:characterclass-fighter-striker": "Fighter: Striker",
  "game:characterdesc-fighter-striker": "Masters of skirmish, weaving between melee and ranged tactics as it best suits the war at hand.",

  "game:characterclass-fighter-looter": "Fighter: Looter",
  "game:characterdesc-fighter-looter": "Opportunists, skulkers, and dungeon delvers. They are as familiar with stabbing a back as they are clubbing a clockwork demon. They are most at home in the depths of the earth or the hazy aftermath of a battle, rifling through the remains for treasures.",

  "game:characterclass-fighter-ranger": "Fighter: Ranger",
  "game:characterdesc-fighter-ranger": "Snipers, specialists, a more honed weapon of war more suited for guerilla tactics over direct confrontation. Their mobility is as unrivaled as their capability with a bow.",

  "game:characterclass-fighter-survivalist": "Fighter: Survivalist",
  "game:characterdesc-fighter-survivalist": "The eyes and ears of any good army. They are more than capable of surviving in the wild for extended periods of reconaissance and remaining self sufficient indefinitely in times of peace.",


  "game:characterclass-oregatherer-miner": "Ore Gatherer: Miner",
  "game:characterdesc-oregatherer-miner": "There are those who brave the shadows of the underworld to reap the much needed metallic resources for civilization, their pickaxes beating like the heart of the Earth herself. These bold miners are no strangers to wearing a little protection to keep themselves protected while they extract every scrap of value they can.",

  "game:characterclass-oregatherer-scrounger": "Ore Gatherer: Scrounger",
  "game:characterdesc-oregatherer-scrounger": "Not all aprove of the wholesale extraction of the minerals from the earth and instead seek to take only what is given freely from the surface and the streams. These little magpies follow their eyes while panning and grazing along the river's edge.",


  "game:characterclass-groundskeeper-hunter": "Groundskeeper: Hunter",
  "game:characterdesc-groundskeeper-hunter": "Responsible for keeping predators at bay as much as they are for keeping the larders stocked with fresh meat. These wily folks are known to bear both bow, spear, and wisdom upon the beasts of the wild.",

  "game:characterclass-groundskeeper-gatherer": "Groundskeeper: Gatherer",
  "game:characterdesc-groundskeeper-gatherer": "Furtive gatherers who seek to make peace with the animals of the woods and act only in self defense. They make up for this by providing a bounty of wild crops and the much-needed seeds to help expand the farmers' plots.",

  "game:characterclass-grovetender-lumberer": "Grovetender: Lumberer",
  "game:characterdesc-grovetender-lumberer": "The grovetender's value is often hard to be seen as their practice takes time but with enough patience, these helpful members can keep the community well supplied with decorative hardwoods, fruit for pies, and ferments. Lumberers increases their effectiveness with lumber-producing trees.",

  "game:characterclass-grovetender-orchardkeeper": "Grovetender: Orchard Keeper",
  "game:characterdesc-grovetender-orchardkeeper": "The grovetender's value is often hard to be seen as their practice takes time but with enough patience, these helpful members can keep the community well supplied with decorative hardwoods, fruit for pies, and ferments. Orchard Keeper sublcass increases their effectiveness with fruit trees.",


  "game:characterclass-farmer-allotmentgardener": "Farmer: Allotment Gardener",
  "game:characterdesc-farmer-allotmentgardener": "Nothing fancy but an absolute essential for any community. These salt of the earth farmers will keep the community and the animals well fed with veggies and grains. Allotment Gardeners increases their effectiveness with vegetables.",

  "game:characterclass-farmer-brewerygardener": "Farmer: Brewery Gardener",
  "game:characterdesc-farmer-brewerygardener": "Nothing fancy but an absolute essential for any community. These salt of the earth farmers will keep the community and the animals well fed with veggies and grains. Brewery Gardeners increases their effectiveness with grains.",

  "game:characterclass-rancher": "Rancher",
  "game:characterdesc-rancher": "Yeehaw! We don't need no grains 'round here. With a rancher in your community, you will be well supplied with good ol'-fashioned protein as they excel at making the most of every animal they harvest.",


  "game:characterclass-healer-druid": "Healer: Druid",
  "game:characterdesc-healer-druid": "These healers are one with the woods. Sure of stride, their hands gentle, and their love for the wild lands unrivaled. They believe in the chaotic joy that is the wildnerness and those who dwell in harmony with it.",

  "game:characterclass-healer-priest": "Healer: Priest",
  "game:characterdesc-healer-priest": "Clerics of grand organizations and knightly orders. Battle-hardened veterans who have been trained in the effecient use of armor to protect themselves whilst maintaining the fighters they stand shoulder to shoulder with.",

  "game:characterclass-healer-shaman": "Healer: Shaman",
  "game:characterdesc-healer-shaman": "Love for their tribe guides their wisdom. Often seen as leaders of warbands and respected not for their strength of arm but their knowledge of the ways of peace as well as war. A battle fought with words is always won, a battle not needed is always lost.",

